# Android-first & UX

Primary ship target: Android (`com.mccloud.weight_sovereignty`). iOS/desktop are out of scope unless requested.

## Android

- Use Flutter APIs first (`wakelock_plus` for workout keep-awake when added) before custom Kotlin
- Respect edge-to-edge and system insets on dashboard; workout session may hide app bar per docs
- Min tap targets: **48dp** general, **56–64dp** for set rows and primary actions in workout mode
- Test on a physical device or emulator with `flutter run`; release signing is debug until configured

## Theme (replace counter-template defaults)

Material 3, dark baseline `#121212`, neutral surfaces, white primary text, one muted accent (deep blue / desaturated green). Low elevation, flat buttons, large numeric typography for weight and reps. No gradients, gamified colors, or decorative chrome.

Workout session: near-black background, high contrast, minimal animation — distinct from dashboard cards.

## Flows (from docs)

1. **Startup** — if no log for today, create `DailyLog` silently
2. **Morning** — if weight missing, large numeric field + save; show Δ vs yesterday
3. **Dashboard** — macros/burn visible immediately; `[+ Food]` → recent/favorites from `FoodConfig`
4. **Workout** — full-screen session; dynamic sets (add/edit/long-press); no modal spam

## Presentation structure

```
presentation/
  app_root.dart          # MaterialApp + theme
  theme/                 # ThemeData extensions (when added)
  screens/               # dashboard, workout_session, food_edit
  widgets/               # shared components
```

Remove template demo UI (`MyHomePage` counter) when implementing real screens — do not extend it.
